<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="plone">

<body>

  <metal:content-core fill-slot="main">

    <header>
      <h1 class="documentFirstHeading">Rebuild zc.relation catalog</h1>
    </header>

    <div id="content-core">

      <h3>
        <span tal:condition="python:view.done">Success!</span>
        Current number of relations in the zc.relation catalog
      </h3>

      <table class="listing table table-striped"
            tal:define="relations_stats python: getattr(view, 'relations_stats', None)"
            tal:condition="python: relations_stats">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Relation</th>
            <th>Amount</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr tal:repeat="item python: sorted(relations_stats)">
            <td>
              <a href=""
                 target="_blank"
                 tal:attributes="href python:'@@inspect-relations?relation={}'.format(item)"
                 tal:content="python:item"
                 title="Inspect relations">
               Type
              </a>
            </td>
            <td tal:content="python:relations_stats[item]">Amount</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Common relations:</h3>
      <dl>
        <dt>relatedItems</dt>
        <dd>Relations between content using the default "Related items" field</dd>

        <dt>isReferencing</dt>
        <dd>Linkintegrity relations (source has a html-link to target)</dd>

        <dt>iterate-working-copy</dt>
        <dd>Relation from content to a working copy (using plone.app.iterate)</dd>

        <dt>staging-working-copy</dt>
        <dd>Outdated relation from content to a working copy (using plone.app.stagingbehavior)</dd>

        <dt>(broken)</dt>
        <dd>Either source or target no longer exist</dd>

        <dt><i>all other</i></dt>
        <dd>Custom attribute/fieldname used to describe the relation</dd>
      </dl>

      <form id="rebuild_relations" method="post" action="@@rebuild-relations" enctype="multipart/form-data">
        <h3>Purge and rebuild relation-catalog</h3>
        <p>Clicking here will do the following:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Get all relations from zc.relation catalog and store them in a annotation on the portal.</li>
          <li>Remove all entries form zc.relation catalog.</li>
          <li>Clean up or flush and rebuild intids - this depends on your selection below</li>
          <li>Restore relations from the annotation on the portal.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="form-check">
          <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" name="flush_and_rebuild_intids" id="flush_intids">
          <label class="form-check-label" for="flush_intids" >Flush and rebuild intids</label>
          <p>
             This will delete all intids and create new one.<br/>
             Warning: If you have a lot of relations this can take some time. Check the log for details!<br/>
             If you have relations on tiles, flushing and rebuilding intids will destroy them b/c intids changed.
          </p>
        </div>
        <button class="context btn btn-danger" type="submit" name="rebuild" value="rebuild" i18n:translate="">Rebuild</button>

      </form>
    </div>

  </metal:content-core>

</body>

</html>
